      • nodeCreateWithLabels

        long nodeCreateWithLabels​(int[] labels)
                   throws ConstraintValidationException
        Create a node, and assign it the given array of labels.

        This method differs from a nodeCreate() and nodeAddLabel(long, int) sequence, in that we will avoid taking the "unlabelled node lock" of the nodeCreate, and we will avoid taking the exclusive node lock in the nodeAddLabel method.

        Parameters:
        labels - The labels to assign to the newly created node.
        Returns:
        The internal id of the created node.
        Throws:
        ConstraintValidationException
